How to prepare better for family photo shoots.
The summer is still in full swing, as soon as possible, the next school year, which families may inherit in their memory.
For everyone to look happy and beautiful in their photos, it is worth considering how to prepare for the photo session in advance.
The advice "Ihappymama" is given by a large-scale mother Aleksandra Nesterenko and professional photographer Marina Levickaja.
It must be photographed in nature, because it is much more natural and harmonious.
The study makes it much more difficult for children to feel and relax.
It is recommended to choose a uniform dress style for the whole family, preferably in one color range.
For example, Aleksandra says that she chooses clothes for all six family members so that the clothes are in no more than three colour shades and as few inscriptions as possible on the clothing.
Don't forget about a good mood.
Have fun, joking, playing, but never shouting or psycho, if the children are not as obedient as they would like.
And here's the next tips already sound from the full of professional photographers!
You need to understand what exactly you want to capture during the photo session and tell the photographer about it.
For some, they will be beautiful, deaf children and an ideal family picture, for others - "life is what it is", that is, the desire to see real, true emotions in the pictures, or, as the photographer loves to say himself, "refuge back", "open eyes", "surprise nose".
Of course, it happens that someone also wants "two in one", but this happens rarely.
In any case, when you go to the photo session, you need to understand that it is just a couple of hours from your life, and the less you get stuck, the better.
You are yourself - there's neither a firm mom who works, is ready to eat, is bringing up, and still does so, nor a father who's always talking on the phone, ever.
And not the man who lives in you behind some unknown shell.
Be a family, remember how great it is to embrace one another, to smile at your own and to have fun.
And then the photographer's task will be to capture the true moments of emotions between you.
If you have chosen a photographer, trust him.
Stop asking 250 times to show what has happened, listen to his advice in choosing clothes, for better shots.
Put on and clean all the clothes you need in advance so you don't have to do it any more on the day of the photo session.
Plan the route and think about how much time you will need to get to the place of the photo session (especially when taking photos at the studio and the time is limited).
If you have little children, choose a time for photo shoot that corresponds to the day-to-day regime so that it doesn't happen at the time when your baby normally sleeps the day.
And, of course, do not forget to take with your children food, cookies, water and favorite toys (to use them only in extreme situations).
