In Parliament's speech, former Minister for War Affairs, Eigan, spoke on behalf of France.
"Discard from the red panties?" he cried out.
Never!
"It's an unspeakable and idiotic supplement to the most visible of all colors," wrote the Messiah later, "there should have been evil consequences."
Leaders of faith who are fighting for women's involvement in leading religious roles could fall into the same trap.
Focusing only on "traditional" religion, rather than asking an important question: "What changes are needed in order for religion to flourish?" they risk losing about 50 percent of their followers.
They also deprive the whole community of the talents, skills and enthusiasm that women would otherwise provide.
To insist that men continue to wear trousers when it comes to religion may be traditional, but this may not be worth it, as the destruction of red bees shows.
